name: Visible Thoughts: 007
description:
007 of the Visible Thoughts series.

I've been writing more lately. My book is progressing better than before, and I guess I owe that to multiple things. Finally moving out on my own, finally feeling a bit more myself, and finally feeling like I'm more in control. These journal pages have helped a lot too. When I was younger, I would write stream-of-conscious all the time with all of my work. Any story, journal, assignment, would all be free-flowing. I knew how to trust my thoughts then. It's different now that I pursued a writing degree. Now my thoughts get in the way of each other, the freeform against the structured. I edit more than I write now, but I'm working on it, and I think I'm getting better. I've found that the more control I have over my life, the less control I exert over my writing. Isn't that strange?
